set1: 03 It's All Over Now Baby Blue 04:54
set2: 03 It's All Over Now Baby Blue 04:54
set3: 03 It's All Over Now Baby Blue 04:54
key_128.comment: Musicians: Jerry Garcia , Bob Weir, *Pigpen, Phil Lesh, Bill Kreutzmann,,Recorded Live at the Avalon Ballroom, San Francisco, 1966  (possibly recorded on September 16 and 17, 1966, which are the nights shown on the Kelly / Mouse poster seen on the cover) Tracks 8, 9 possibly recorded on November 1966 at The Matrix, San Francisco,,Produced and Engineered by Robert Cohen,(Tracks 8,9 Produced by Peter Abram),Edit and Remix by Richard Delvy,,Cover art - John Pierce, Mokelvey (Vintage),Back cover photos - Baron Wolman (Vintage),Poster design - Kelly / Mouse Studios (Vintage),Ripple Bottle by Gallo (Vintage),Album design - Robert Hickson (Historic),,Original LP master tapes remastered for CD at Polygram (1995) > DAT > CDR,,Background on these LPs:,These 2 LPs were release without explicit permission from the Dead.Producer Robert Cohen (a bit more on Mr. Cohen here: http://www.lumiereprod.com/history.html) got the masters from recordingsmade at the Avalon, adding applause and other sounds where needed to helpthe flow (there is a bit of audio, a small segment with some mostlyinaudible band chatter, which was added to "extend" tracks so theywouldn't end so abruptly.  The same segment used in a couple of differentspots, once as a loop that repeats 2-3 times).  Some of the songs have cutintros, but are segued with applause anyway.  These are pretty muchbootleg quality from today's perspective, and frankly most interest inthese LPs is because of their status as collectibles rather than beingworthwhile musically.  But fans of the early days will especially enjoythe lengthy workouts of "Midnight Hour", "The Same Thing" and "GoodMorning Little Schoolgirl".,,Some info on the Sunflower label:,http://www.bsnpubs.com/mgm/sunflower.html,,Footnote: An LP released in 1973, "The History Of The Grateful Dead"(Pride/MGM PRD-0016), compiled the following tracks from the SunflowerLPs: Dancin' In The Street, It's All Over Now, Baby Blue, I Know YouRider, In The Midnight Hour, It Hurts Me Too, Lindy and Stealin'.  Therewas also an official release on Warners released in 1973 with virtuallythe same title (subtitled "Bear's Choice", as we all know), so the PrideLP couldn't have been very welcome at that time.
